  <div class="container">
    <h1>Self Learning Trading Bot</h1>
    <p>A trading bot with an 80% success rate that shows the strategy it used.</p>
    <h2>Strategy:</h2>
    <p>The trading bot uses a combination of technical indicators and machine learning algorithms to make trading decisions. It analyzes historical price data, market trends, and other relevant factors to identify potential profitable trades.</p>
    <p>Here are some key features of the trading bot:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Technical Indicators: The bot utilizes popular technical indicators such as moving averages, RSI (Relative Strength Index), MACD (Moving Average Convergence Divergence), and Bollinger Bands to identify entry and exit points.</li>
      <li>Machine Learning: The bot incorporates machine learning algorithms to continuously learn and adapt to market conditions. It analyzes past trades and adjusts its strategy based on the outcomes.</li>
      <li>Risk Management: The bot implements risk management techniques to protect the trading capital. It sets stop-loss and take-profit levels for each trade to minimize losses and maximize profits.</li>
      <li>Backtesting: The bot allows users to backtest their trading strategies using historical data. This helps in evaluating the performance of different strategies and fine-tuning them.</li>
      <li>Real-Time Trading: The bot connects to various exchanges through API integrations and executes trades in real-time. It provides live updates on open positions, account balance, and overall portfolio performance.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Success Rate:</h2>
    <p>The trading bot has an impressive success rate of 80%. This means that out of every 10 trades, it correctly predicts the market movement and generates profits in 8 trades on average.</p>
    <h2>Example Trade:</h2>
    <p>Here is an example of how the trading bot executes a trade:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Indicator Analysis: The bot identifies a bullish signal based on the crossover of the 50-day moving average above the 200-day moving average.</li>
      <li>Entry Point: The bot enters a long position when the price breaks above the resistance level and confirms the bullish trend.</li>
      <li>Stop-Loss and Take-Profit: The bot sets a stop-loss order below the recent swing low and a take-profit order at a predefined target level.</li>
      <li>Monitoring and Exit: The bot continuously monitors the trade and adjusts the stop-loss and take-profit levels based on market conditions. It exits the trade when the price reaches the take-profit level or hits the stop-loss level.</li>
    </ul>
    <h2>Disclaimer:</h2>
    <p>Trading in financial markets involves risks, and past performance is not indicative of future results. The success rate mentioned is based on historical data and may vary in different market conditions. It is recommended to consult with a financial advisor before engaging in any trading activities.</p>
